<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Oh Elon</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In some parallel universe, Elon Musk=E2=80=99s=
 dispute with Twitter Inc. is about how many bots there are on Twitter. In =
that universe, Twitter=E2=80=99s merger agreement with Musk contains a repr=
esentation=C2=A0that no more than 5% of Twitter=E2=80=99s monetizable daily=
 active users, or mDAUs, are bots, Musk=E2=80=99s obligation to close the m=
erger is contingent on this representation being true,=C2=A0and Musk has di=
scovered that it is=C2=A0wrong. Therefore he is able to walk away from the =
agreement, and maybe even sue Twitter for damages for misleading him.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In our actual universe none of this is true. I=
n the real world, Musk signed a merger agreement with Twitter, and it was p=
ublicly filed, and you can <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/28414941.263594/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYX=
RhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMTIwNDYxL2QzMTA4NDNkZXgyMS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8=
524a319a23cB7dd41769/email" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;">read it here</a>. That merger agreement=
=C2=A0<em>does not mention bots at all</em>. In pursuing and signing this d=
eal, Musk <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28414941=
.263594/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDU=
tMTcvZWxvbi1tdXNrLWRvZXMtbm90LWNhcmUtYWJvdXQtc3BhbS1ib3RzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA3MT=
gyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0b=
V90ZXJtPTIyMDcxOCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB=
c5970316/email" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;"> was excited about =E2=80=9Cdefeating=E2=80=9D</a> =
the bots, sure, but he didn=E2=80=99t care how many there were. (The more o=
f them there are, the more glory in defeating them.)=C2=A0He did not do any=
 due diligence on the number of bots before signing the agreement, nor did =
he ask Twitter to make any promises about how many=C2=A0bots there were. No=
thing in the negotiations over the deal, or in the merger agreement itself,=
 was in any way contingent on anything at all about bots.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now, even in the real world, the merger agreem=
ent=C2=A0<em>does=C2=A0</em>contain <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/28414941.263594/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZ=
Gdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMTk1MTI2L2QyODMxMTlkcHJlcjE0YS5odG0j=
YW54YXRvYzI4MzExOV8yMw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7332f39a/email" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">a r=
epresentation</a> that none of Twitter=E2=80=99s filings with the US Securi=
ties and Exchange Commission=C2=A0=E2=80=9Ccontained any untrue statement o=
f a material fact.=E2=80=9D And if that representation <a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28414941.263594/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLm=
dvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMTk1MTI2L2QyODMxM=
TlkcHJlcjE0YS5odG0jYW54YXRvYzI4MzExOV83Mg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2859935f=
/email" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;">is false enough</a> to have a =E2=80=9Cmaterial adverse eff=
ect=E2=80=9D on Twitter, then Musk can get out of the deal.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And Twitter=E2=80=99s SEC filings=C2=A0<em>do=
=C2=A0</em>mention bots. But they don=E2=80=99t=C2=A0contain any promises t=
hat no more than 5% of Twitter=E2=80=99s users are bots. These filings are =
also public, and you can also read them. Here is <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28414941.263594/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9p=
eD9kb2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMTQxODA5MS8wMDAxNDE4MDkxMjIwMDAwNzUvdHd=
0ci0yMDIyMDMzMS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB62812840/email" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" title=3D"page 5" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">what they say about bots</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are a number of false or spa=
m accounts in existence on our platform.=C2=A0We have performed an internal=
 review of a sample of accounts and estimate that the average of false or s=
pam accounts during the first quarter of 2022 represented fewer than 5% of =
our mDAU during the quarter. The false or spam accounts for a period repres=
ents the average of false or spam accounts in the samples during each month=
ly analysis period during the quarter. In making this determination, we app=
lied significant judgment, so our estimation of false or spam accounts may =
not accurately represent the actual number of such accounts, and the actual=
 number of false or spam accounts could be higher than we have estimated.</=
p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Let=E2=80=99s pick out the factual assertions =
in that paragraph:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">There are =E2=80=9Cfalse or spam acco=
unts=E2=80=9D on Twitter.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Twitter =
reviews some sample accounts each month.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom:=
 5px;">It estimates, based on that review,=C2=A0that the bots (false or spa=
m accounts) are fewer than 5% of mDAUs.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: =
5px;">That estimate is based on the =E2=80=9Caverage of false or spam accou=
nts in the samples.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">That =
estimate, and the labeling of spam accounts, is subjective; Twitter =E2=80=
=9Capplied significant judgment=E2=80=9D to reach it.</li>=09<li style=3D"m=
argin-bottom: 5px;">=E2=80=9CThe actual number of false or spam accounts co=
uld be higher than we have estimated.=E2=80=9D</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You could imagine how some of those statements=
 could be false.=C2=A0If Twitter did not review any sample accounts =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0if it just made up the 5% number and put it in the filings =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0then its SEC filings would be false. If it reviewed its samples an=
d labeled 25% of them spam, and then wrote 5% in the filings anyway, then t=
he filings would be false.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand. If you said to Twitter =E2=
=80=9Clook, I don=E2=80=99t like how you sample accounts, and I really don=
=E2=80=99t like how you evaluate them for spam.=C2=A0I have developed a bet=
ter way to identify spam accounts, and when I apply my method to a differen=
t sample I conclude that 8% of your mDAUs are spam,=E2=80=9D and Twitter lo=
oked at your method and said =E2=80=9Coh, wow, you know what, you are entir=
ely right in every respect, this is better, 8% of our mDAUs are spam=E2=80=
=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0then nothing in Twitter=E2=80=99s SEC filings would be f=
alse. (I suppose they=E2=80=99d have to write something different in=C2=A0<=
em>future=C2=A0</em>filings.) The filings said that their numbers were esti=
mates, that they applied significant judgment, and that the actual number m=
ight be higher. If you said =E2=80=9CI have a better estimate with better j=
udgment, and the numbers are higher,=E2=80=9D they could reasonably respond=
 =E2=80=9Cyes, right, exactly like we said.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Of course, if Twitter=E2=80=99s quarterly repo=
rts were wildly wrong about its operating or financial results, then that w=
ould be bad, even if Twitter prefaced those reports by saying =E2=80=9Chere=
=E2=80=99s our best guess but we might be wrong.=E2=80=9D But the bot numbe=
rs, and the related numbers of monetizable daily active users, are not part=
 of Twitter=E2=80=99s financial results. US generally accepted accounting p=
rinciples do not cover bots or mDAUs, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/28414941.263594/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9peD9kb2M9L0F=
