rket=E2=80=99s decline over the last few months (which makes this deal look=
 more expensive and less attractive to Musk) but by real concern about Twit=
ter=E2=80=99s ability to count bots. As I argue in the text, I don=E2=80=99=
t think this is particularly relevant to Musk=E2=80=99s obligation to close=
 the deal, but it does make his position more sympathetic. In his lawyers=
=E2=80=99 telling, his concerns were triggered not by the market drop but b=
y <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28414941.263594/=
aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTQxODA=
5MTIyMDAwMDcyL3R3dHJxMTIyZXg5OTEuaHRt/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9b2d7742/ema=
il" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">Twitter=E2=80=99s disclosure</a>, three days after signing, th=
at it had incorrectly calculated some of its daily active user numbers for =
years. The mistake was big enough to require updating the historical number=
s, though small enough that even Musk=E2=80=99s lawyers don=E2=80=99t argue=
 that it was material to the deal. (Some quarterly counts were off by about=
 1%.) We talked about this restatement <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/28414941.263594/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcG=
luaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMjgvZWxvbi1tdXNrLXMtb3RoZXItbWVyZ2VyLXdvcmtlZ=
C1vdXQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDcxODIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291=
cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwNzE4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBed4be726/email" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> at the time</a>, and I expl=
ained that it was obviously not big enough to be a =E2=80=9Cmaterial advers=
e effect=E2=80=9D that could get Musk out of the deal, and it looks like hi=
s lawyers agree. But I also said that, if Twitter knew about the mistake be=
fore the merger agreement was signed =E2=80=94 which seemed likely to me, s=
ince they disclosed it publicly just three days later =E2=80=94 then they s=
hould have disclosed it to Musk before signing the deal. But his filing say=
s they didn=E2=80=99t: =E2=80=9COn April 28, just three days after signing =
the Agreement, Twitter restated three years of its mDAU numbers, despite ne=
ver disclosing the issue to Defendants pre-signing.=E2=80=9D I =E2=80=A6 th=
at=E2=80=99s weird? They should have disclosed that? </p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-2" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[2] Musk=E2=80=99s lawyers don=E2=80=99t argue=
 that automation or AI or machine learning would be better or anything; the=
y just expect everyone to think =E2=80=9Coh of course, AI.=E2=80=9D Presuma=
bly you would use human judgment to train the AI? But, sure, if you want to=
 decide whose approach is better, you would need to examine facts and talk =
to experts and get a sense of the debate. My point is that there is no reas=
on for the court to care whose approach is better, because that simply isn=
=E2=80=99t relevant to anyone=E2=80=99s obligations under the merger agreem=
ent.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-3" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[3] Similarly, one of Musk=E2=80=99s lawyers=
=E2=80=99 letters to Twitter from May =E2=80=94 included in <a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28414941.263594/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc=
2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMTk1MTI2L2Qy=
ODMxMTlkcHJlcjE0YS5odG0jdG9jMjgzMTE5XzUx/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd83e00b9/=
email" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;">Twitter=E2=80=99s latest revised proxy statement</a> =E2=80=
=94 says that =E2=80=9CMr. Musk was surprised to learn of the lax methodolo=
gies that Twitter employs to assess the actual prevalence of fake or spam a=
ccounts on its platform,=E2=80=9D and that =E2=80=9CMr. Musk requested that=
 Twitter apply more rigorous computer-aided and third-party testing to dete=
rmine the prevalence of fake or spam accounts on its platform with greater =
certainty.=E2=80=9D Again, that is totally a thing that he can do, when he =
buys Twitter: If he owns the company, he is free to tell it how to run its =
business. He just has to buy it first. </p>
</div>
